Codes DUPOL and DUPPG 2.3.68

Background: CFOL command code (CC) DUPOL is designed to research display information to assist in fraud detection of SSNs in both paper and tronically ﬁled returns. CC DUPOL extracts taxpayer information from the Duplicate TIN database that contains tax return information for the Tax Pro- cessing years 2021, 2022 and 2023. Command Code DUPPG is a subsidiary command code, and provides a second page–when available—of Duplicate TIN data once DUPOL has been used for the ﬁrst page.
Purpose: These sections provide instructions for accessing Duplicate TIN in- formation through the Duplicate TIN (DUPTIN) database ﬁles in Martinsburg,

CC DUPOL will display Nationwide and individual Service Center counts of how many times a particular SSN was used for the desired year. These counts will only be displayed on the ﬁrst screen if multiple pages exist. CC DUPOL will display how many times the SSN was used, how it was used, and who used it. CC DUPOL will provide IDRS
like paging when multiple records exist.

The paging routine will automatically position the cursor following the Start of Message symbol. When the ENTER key is depressed, the terminal will display the next page or any page designated by overlaying a page number onto the format by key input.
In the event of an error situation, one of the following messages will be issued:

In the event of an error situation, one of the following messages will be a. INVALID TIN REQUEST - Taxpayer Identiﬁcation Number is improperly formatted or non-numeric. b. NO RECORD FOUND IN TABLE - There is no information for the requested Taxpayer Identiﬁcation Number in the Duplicate TIN ﬁle. c. CHECK TIN AND RE-ENTER REQUEST - Check Taxpayer Number and re-attempt request. d. DUPOL FILE NOT AVAILABLE - TRY LATER - The attempt to access Duplicate TIN Database failed. e. UNSUCCESSFUL READ CAUSED BY TIME-OUT - The CC request canceled due to the length of turnaround time. f. NO RECORD FOUND IN PRIMARY LINK TABLE - The requested SSN indicates multiple use but no information exist on ﬁle. g. ERROR DETECTED IN RETRIEVING DATA, CONTACT - The attempt to retrieve data from DB

ﬁle encountered a severe error and the program abended. h. ERROR DETECTED WHILE OPENING CURSOR, CONTACT PRO- GRAMMER - The attempt to read multiple records resulted in a severe error. i. ERROR DETECTED WHILE CLOSING CURSOR, CONTACT PRO- GRAMMER - The attempt to close ﬁle resulted in a severe error. j. SQL ERROR ENCOUNTERED: (error code) - The program aborted due a DB
system error. Contact IBM Database Administration Section for frontline investigation and resolution. If further investigation cites a DB

systems error, problem will be escalated to appropriate IBM Database Support Section by the production DBA as mandated by existing Service Level Agreements. k. A PAGING REQUEST WAS ENTERED BEFORE A DUPOL REQUEST WAS ENTERED - an attempt to retrieve an additional page was before an initial DUPOL request was made. l. NO SCREENS AVAILABLE - The attempt to retrieve an additional screen was unsuccessful, no additional screen exists. m. INVALID TRANSACTION REQUEST - The CC request was invalid due a missing or invalid deﬁner code. n. (n) PLAN DEFINER NOT AVAILABLE YET - A deﬁner was used that is one of the three current deﬁners (
